The paper discusses the use of multi-agent systems and heuristics to solve the ridesharing problem, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the need for scalable solutions, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The use of relocation schemes to improve QoS metrics could fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the evaluation of different algorithms could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
